s/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">→d[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.fderivD\">fderivD</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">u</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">v</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap.evalCLM\">SchwartzMap.evalCLM</a> <span class=\"fn\">v</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap.fderivCLM\">SchwartzMap.fderivCLM</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.fderivD_apply","kind":"theorem","line":232,"name":"Distribution.fderivD_apply","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L232-L234"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.fderivD\"><span class=\"name\">Distribution</span>.<span class=\"name\">fderivD</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E </span><span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Action/Defs.html#SMulCommClass\">SMulCommClass</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional/Defs.html#FiniteDimensional\">FiniteDimensional</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">→d[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">→d[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">→L[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Fréchet derivative of a distribution.\n\nInformally, for a distribution `u : E →d[𝕜] F`,\nthe Fréchet derivative `fderiv u x v` corresponds to the derivative of `u` at the\npoint `x` in the direction `v`. For example, if `F = ℝ³`\nthen `fderiv u x v` is a vector in `ℝ³` corresponding to\n`(v₁ ∂u₁/∂x₁ + v₂ ∂u₁/∂x₂ + v₃ ∂u₁/∂x₃, v₁ ∂u₂/∂x₁ + v₂ ∂u₂/∂x₂ + v₃ ∂u₂/∂x₃,...)`.\n\nFormally, for a distribution `u : E →d[𝕜] F`, this is actually defined\nthe distribution which takes test function `η : E → 𝕜` to\n`- u (SchwartzMap.evalCLM v (SchwartzMap.fderivCLM 𝕜 η))`.\n\nNote that, unlike for functions, the Fréchet derivative of a distribution always exists.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.fderivD","kind":"def","line":165,"name":"Distribution.fderivD","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L165-L230"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.ofLinear_apply\"><span class=\"name\">Distribution</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofLinear_apply</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E </span><span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">u</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hu</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>),\n    <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>       <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>),\n        <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>), <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\">k</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/FTaylorSeries.html#iteratedFDeriv\">iteratedFDeriv</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <span class=\"fn\">(⇑<span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.ofLinear\">ofLinear</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">u</span> <span class=\"fn\">hu</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.ofLinear_apply","kind":"theorem","line":139,"name":"Distribution.ofLinear_apply","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L139-L144"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.ofLinear\"><span class=\"name\">Distribution</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofLinear</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E </span><span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">u</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hu</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>),\n    <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>       <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/SchwartzSpace.html#SchwartzMap\">SchwartzMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>),\n        <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>), <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\">k</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/FTaylorSeries.html#iteratedFDeriv\">iteratedFDeriv</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <span class=\"fn\">(⇑<span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">→d[</a><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The construction of a distribution from the following data:\n1. We take a finite set `s` of pairs `(k, n) ∈ ℕ × ℕ` that will be explained later.\n2. We take a linear map `u` that evaluates the given Schwartz function `η`. At this stage we don't\n  need `u` to be continuous.\n3. Recall that a Schwartz function `η` satisfies a bound\n  `‖x‖ᵏ * ‖(dⁿ/dxⁿ) η‖ < Mₙₖ` where `Mₙₖ : ℝ` only depends on `(k, n) : ℕ × ℕ`.\n4. This step is where `s` is used: for each test function `η`, the norm `‖u η‖` is required to be\n  bounded by `C * (‖x‖ᵏ * ‖(dⁿ/dxⁿ) η‖)` for some `x : ℝ` and for some `(k, n) ∈ s`, where\n  `C ≥ 0` is a global scalar.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution.ofLinear","kind":"def","line":116,"name":"Distribution.ofLinear","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L116-L137"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#«term_→d[_]_»\"><span class=\"name\">«term_→d[_]_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An `F`-valued distribution on `E` (where `E` is a normed vector space over `ℝ` and `F` is a\nnormed vector space over `𝕜`) is a continuous linear map `𝓢(E, 𝕜) →L[𝕜] F` where `𝒮(E, 𝕜)` is\nthe Schwartz space of smooth functions `E → 𝕜` with rapidly decreasing iterated derivatives. This\nis notated as `E →d[𝕜] F`.\n\nThis should be seen as a generalisation of functions `E → F`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#«term_→d[_]_»","kind":"def","line":95,"name":"«term_→d[_]_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L95-L95"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution\"><span class=\"name\">Distribution</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜 </span><span class=\"fn\">E </span><span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An `F`-valued distribution on `E` (where `E` is a normed vector space over `ℝ` and `F` is a\nnormed vector space over `𝕜`) is a continuous linear map `𝓢(E, 𝕜) →L[𝕜] F` where `𝒮(E, 𝕜)` is\nthe Schwartz space of smooth functions `E → 𝕜` with rapidly decreasing iterated derivatives. This\nis notated as `E →d[𝕜] F`.\n\nThis should be seen as a generalisation of functions `E → F`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/Distribution/Basic.html#Distribution","kind":"def","line":85,"name":"Distribution","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L85-L93"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Distribution.FourierSchwartz","PhysLean.Meta.TODO.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.Mathematics.Distribution.Basic"}